column1: Who will win the 2020 Golden Globe for Best Performance by an Actress in a Motion Picture - Musical or Comedy?
column5: ['Ana de Armas (Knives Out)', 'Awkwafina (The Farewell)', "Cate Blanchett (Where'd You Go, Bernadette)", 'Beanie Feldstein (Booksmart)', 'Emma Thompson (Late Night)', 'A tie or other outcome']

column6: Hard to bet against either Emma Thompson or Cate Blanchett, so they are my two favorites, with Ana de Armas as the buzz-getting underdog.
I have not seen any of these films. My forecasts are solely based upon popularity (of a book), 'buzz' and/or press.
Based on current visibility and press coverage.
